Fears of maize shortage rise as rains delay crop harvest             Mt Kenya Star  10th Feb 2020 10:04:35 GMT +0300 Mt Kenya Star  10th Feb 2020 10:04:35 GMT +0300 Mt Kenya Star   Harvesting machine designed to efficiently harvest a variety of grain crops lies idle in the yard as farmers wait for the rains to subdue before they embark on getting their crop from the farms. There have been warning of shortage of maize in the country.  Harvesting machine designed to efficiently harvest a variety of grain crops lies idle in the yard as farmers wait for the rains to subdue before they embark on getting their crop from the farms. There have been warning of shortage of maize in the country. Harvesting machine designed to efficiently harvest a variety of grain crops lies idle in the yard as farmers wait for the rains to subdue before they embark on getting their crop from the farms. There have been warning of shortage of maize in the country.         For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Subscribe Now » For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Subscribe Now » Subscribe Now » Wait and see tactic           Longer duration             Road network problem                 Reports by Wangechi Waithera, Mugucia Rugene and Willies Mwaniki.  Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. HERE.  #mc_embed_signup{background:#fff; clear:left; font:14px Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; }
